{
 "name": "RPlog_Across_the_Force",
 "title": "Across the Force",
 "summary": "Adrift in the silvery dreamscape of the Force, the wounded Orson meditates while brooding over Jessalyn's apparent turn to the dark side and her decision to change allegiances. Unintentionally his consciousness brushes against the sleeping Jessalyn, who has been hiding with Simon in the sewers and whose mental barriers against the Force have begun to dissolve. The two former companions speak across the distance: she begs him to leave her alone and to fulfill his destiny without mourning her, insisting she cannot return to the Jedi tainted as she is, while Orson refuses to abandon her, admitting only that he was not strong enough for her. A childhood memory surfaces of a five-year-old Jessalyn on a landing pad, offering wildflowers to the departing Dr. Xavier Nighman, the one adult who ever cared for her, before he leaves her behind. As the fragile contact frays, Orson is reeled back across the Force and wakes at the Uwannabuyim's workstation, whispering that had the Jedi asked him months ago whether he wished to learn the Force, he would have said no.",
